{"1": {"comment_id": "nutrition_facts_org"  "comment_text": "Here is a simple and delicious Daily Dozen inspired meal to make this weekend: Red Beans and Quinoa. Recipe is from Jenny  our Development Director.

INGREDIENTS:
2 lemons
1 medium onion  chopped
1 large bell pepper  chopped
1 cup of chopped celery
1 1/2 cups cooked or 1 (15.5-ounce) BPA-free can or Tetra Pak salt-free kidney beans  drained and rinsed
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 teaspoon dried oregano
1/2 teaspoon paprika
1/4-1/2 teaspoon black pepper
1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder
1/4 teaspoon cayenne
1/4- 1/2 cup of no-salt added vegetable broth or water*
Cooked quinoa  to serve

METHOD:
1. Heat the juice of two lemons in a pot over medium heat and sauteÌ the chopped onion  bell pepper  and celery.
2. Once the veggies are soft  add in the kidney beans  spices  and vegetable broth. Stir everything together and simmer for a few minutes. Cook until the dish is heated thoroughly.
3. Serve with the cooked quinoa and enjoy!
Makes enough for about 3-4 people

*The Light Vegetable Broth from the How Not to Diet Cookbook is here: https://nutritionfacts.org/recipe/light-vegetable-broth/

main_text: Lectins can do WHAT â‰ï¸Lectins are stable in an acidic environment which is why they donâ€™t get broken down by our stomach enzymes ğŸ¦  They then enter our small intestine and then the bloodstreağŸ©¸ Lectins have been cited as the cause of ğŸ‘‡ğŸ¼ğŸ¥” Some autoimmune diseasesğŸ¥œ Chronic inflammationğŸŒ½ ObesityPeople can be so sensitive that even a small amount will cause a reaction. For example raw and/or uncooked kidney bean in the smallest amount have been known to cause severe nausea vomiting and diarrhea because of â€œphytohemagglutininâ€ which is a type of lectin that binds to red blood cells once it passes into the bloodstream.If you are experiencing symptoms like diarrhea nausea fatigue or vomiting itâ€™s best to be aware of the foods that have a high lectin content and treat it.The most common treatment is a lectin-avoidance diet. main_text: Mexican RiceIt is sure to liven up your day. It is zesty & flavorful vegan dish. We all love fried rice but I realized it was time to change it up with this restaurant style Mexican rice. This rice comes together so easily & quickly in a single pot which makes for an easy clean-up. This Mexican rice features hearty long-grained rice sauted with tomato purry & lots of veggies kidney beans & spices.Process1. First rinse 1 cup of long grained rice under cold running water a few times . This gets the starches out so that the rice doesnâ€™t become sticky or mushy when stir fried.2. Next over medium heat pan add tbsp oil butter then add tomato purry spices chilli flakes & oregano then add ketchup in it & boil on high flame.3. Then add salsa sauce (In a mixer add little bit tomatoes jalapennos coriandersaltlemon grind it in semi-liquid form)4. Now add veggies like bell pepper capsicum sweet corn olives jalapennos & lastly qdd boiled kidney beans.5. Now add the drained rice to the hot pan. Mix well & stir continously as you saute the rice on the low heat. The putside of tge rice should start to het slightly beowned & lightly toasted but be careful that they do not burn.6. Now add 2 cups of vegetable stock/hot water depending on the quality of of ricr you are using mix well. Cover & cook the rice on a low heat for about 20-22 mins or untill tye rice grains qre tender  fluffy & all the liquids have been absorbed.7. Serve the Mexican rice hot in plate then add salsa sauce on top of it pieces of tortilla chips cheess then again repeat same steps.8. comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mishthefoodicon"  "comment_text": "Mexican Rice
It is sure to liven up your day. It is zesty & flavorful vegan dish. We all love fried rice  but I realized it was time to change it up with this restaurant style Mexican rice. This rice comes together so easily & quickly in a single pot  which makes for an easy clean-up. This Mexican rice features hearty long-grained rice  sauted with tomato purry & lots of veggies  kidney beans & spices.

Process
1. First rinse 1 cup of long grained rice under cold running water a few times . This gets the starches out so that the rice doesnâ€™t become sticky or mushy when stir fried.
2. Next over  medium heat pan add tbsp oil  butter then add tomato purry  spices  chilli flakes & oregano then add ketchup in it & boil on high flame.
3. Then add salsa sauce (In a mixer add little bit tomatoes  jalapennos  coriander salt lemon grind it in semi-liquid form)
4. Now add veggies like bell pepper  capsicum  sweet corn  olives  jalapennos & lastly qdd boiled kidney beans.
5. Now add the drained rice to the hot pan. Mix well & stir continously as you saute the rice on the low heat. The putside of tge rice should start to het slightly beowned & lightly toasted  but be careful that they do not burn.
6. Now add 2 cups of vegetable stock/hot water depending on the quality of of ricr you are using  mix well. Cover & cook the rice on a low heat for about 20-22 mins or untill tye rice grains qre tender   fluffy & all the liquids have been absorbed.
7. Serve the Mexican rice hot in plate then add salsa sauce on top of it  pieces of tortilla chips  cheess then again repeat same steps.
8. Garnish it with some olives jalapennos basil leaves

Follow: @mishthefoodicon

main_text: Rajma-Chawal! ğŸ›/** Rajma-Chawal recipe **/Disclaimer: This is my version of Rajma as this is what suits my taste buds light on the tummy and easy on spices. Please feel free to add/modify ingredients based on your preferences.1. In a pressure cooker add 1 slit green chilli along with 5 chopped garlic pods and sautÃ© for a few seconds.2.Add 1 large onion finely chopped and sautÃ© until golden brown.3.Add 2 medium-sized tomatoes and let soften.4.Add ginger-garlic paste and sautÃ© until the raw smell goes off.5.Now turn your flame low and add spices such as 1 tbspn kashmiri chilli powder 1 tspn turmeric powder 1 tbspn dhaniya-Zeera powder 1 tspn garam masala powder 1.5 tspn chaat masala and salt according to taste.6.After bhunofying these masalas along with the onion-tomatoes on a low flame add the Rajma(soaked overnight) and mix well.7.At this point also add finely chopped coriander and a dash of lime juice approx 1 tbspn.8.Add water just enough to soak the Rajma not too much not too little.9.Pressure cook for 4 whistles or until soft but not mushy.10.Let cool and eventually garnish with more finely chopped coriander.11.Goes well with both rice and chapati.#lunchspecial #rajma #rajmachawal #chawal #kidneybeans #redkidneybeans #steamedrice
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "lubnasfoodgram"  "comment_text": "Rajma-Chawal! ğŸ›

/** Rajma-Chawal recipe **/

Disclaimer: This is my version of Rajma as this is what suits my taste buds  light on the tummy and easy on spices. Please feel free to add/modify ingredients based on your preferences.

1. In a pressure cooker  add 1 slit green chilli along with 5 chopped garlic pods and sautÃ© for a few seconds.
2.Add 1 large onion finely chopped and sautÃ© until golden brown.
3.Add 2 medium-sized tomatoes and let soften.
4.Add ginger-garlic paste and sautÃ© until the raw smell goes off.
5.Now turn your flame low and add spices such as 1 tbspn kashmiri chilli powder  1 tspn turmeric powder  1 tbspn dhaniya-Zeera powder  1 tspn garam masala powder  1.5 tspn chaat masala and salt according to taste.
6.After bhunofying these masalas along with the onion-tomatoes on a low flame  add the Rajma(soaked overnight) and mix well.
7.At this point  also add finely chopped coriander and a dash of lime juice  approx 1 tbspn.
8.Add water just enough to soak the Rajma  not too much not too little.
9.Pressure cook for 4 whistles or until soft but not mushy.
10.Let cool and eventually garnish with more finely chopped coriander.
11.Goes well with both rice and chapati.
